messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/users/{id}

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

Methods allowed (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the user routes at the prefix /api/users via app.use('/api/users', userRoutes).
- routes/userRoutes.js defines router.route('/:id') with the following method handlers:
  - .delete(protect, admin, deleteUser) → DELETE is implemented
  - .get(protect, admin, getUserById) → GET is implemented
  - .put(protect, admin, updateUser) → PUT is implemented
- The controller userController.js contains the corresponding implementations for getUserById (GET), updateUser (PUT), and deleteUser (DELETE).
- There is no router.all or any other catch-all that would allow every HTTP method, so "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false.
- For HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, POST, PATCH there are no explicit route handlers in the code for the path '/:id', so they are marked false. (Per your instruction, this determination is made strictly from the code rather than runtime framework behaviors.)
